-- Spot Gold Declines as Much as 0.4%, Reversing Earlier Gain; Silver Drops
-- B y   S u n g w o o   P a r k
-- 2010-11-15T06:05:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-15/spot-gold-declines-as-much-as-0-4-reversing-earlier-gain-silver-drops.html
Gold for immediate delivery dropped
as much as 0.4 percent to $1,363.50 an ounce, reversing earlier
gains. The metal traded 0.3 percent lower at $1,364.70 an ounce
at 3:04 p.m. in Seoul.  Immediate-delivery silver lost as much as 0.7 percent to
$25.8850 an ounce and last traded at $25.945 an ounce.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sungwoo Park in Seoul at 
